{
  "stem": "3012.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We heard about ghettos.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we never heard about the Einsatzgruppen.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We never heard about the camps.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But one day, a neighbor's mail got mixed up with our mail.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was a card, which we inadvertently read because it was in our mail.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Probably between '42 and '44.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it said-- it came from the Russian front, written by an officer-- we are system-- this is a direct quote-- 'We are systematically exterminating the Jews.' Unquote.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Written by the officer to his family in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Of course, today we know what that means.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's-- it's a mobile killing unit.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's the Einsatzgruppen.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It's-- with the aid of Hungarians and Ukrainians [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and the rest of them.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the SS, mainly.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We-- we-- we suspected that this is just some-- some local atrocity.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We-- we-- we couldn't even imagine that this was the beginning of the final solution-- of the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't remember, but the postcard was given or mailed-- I don't know how-- to the person to whom it belonged.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How, and where, and by whom, I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I heard it from-- I heard it either from my aunt, [INAUDIBLE], or from my parents.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm not sure anymore.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not at that time.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On the 19th of March, 1944, a friend of mine called from-- I believe it was the Ministry of Foreign Affairs-- that the Nazis crossed the Hungarian border and they were approaching Budapest.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was an early morning call.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I knew that the Berlin Express is leaving Budapest at 2:00 PM, and I could be on it if I pulled myself together.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
